.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-3-14::.
There 6 different types of food: onion, corn, strawberry, lime, mango, pineapple
The people use 6 different means of transport: bike, taxi, scooter, subway, skateboard, quad-bike
 1. the person eating strawberry is on the right of the person eating corn##1
 2. the person driving the scooter is on the left or right of the person eating onion##3
 3. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the person driving the bike##1
 4. the person driving the skateboard is on the left or right of the person eating pineapple##3
 5. the person eating lime is on the right of the person eating strawberry##1
 6. the person driving the quad-bike is on the far left or far right##3
 7. the person eating mango is between the person driving the subway and the person driving the taxi##2
 8. the person driving the bike is the person eating strawberry##1
 9. the person driving the bike is on the right of the person driving the skateboard##1
10. the person eating onion is the person driving the taxi##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |   2    |    3     |     4     |     5      |   6    |
| Food        | onion  | mango | pineapple | corn | strawberry   | lime |
| Transport   | taxi | scooter | subway    | skateboard     | bike | quad-bike    |

